Action.c(23):           if (goToObj.select) goToObj.select();\n
Action.c(23):           if (goToObj.focus) goToObj.focus();\n
Action.c(23):         }\n
Action.c(23):         if (!allAtOnce) {return false};\n
Action.c(23):       }\n

Action.c(23):         if (alertText != "") {\n
Action.c(23):           alert(alertText);\n
Action.c(23):           return false;\n
Action.c(23):         }\n
Action.c(23):       } \n

Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(23):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(23):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(23):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(23):     **     text\n
Action.c(23):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(23):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(23):     **     radio\n
Action.c(23):     **     select\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(23):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(23):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(23):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     // object definition\n
Action.c(23):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(23):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(23):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(23):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(23):     }\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ** var phoneNum = new validation('phone number', 'phoneNum', 'text', 'isPhoneNum(str)', 'x
Action.c(23):     xx-xxx-xxxx');\n
Action.c(23):     ** var reason = new validation('reason for reading this', 'reason', 'checkbox', 'isCheck(f
Action.c(23):     ormObj, form, 14, 3)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     // create objects here:\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     var username = new validation('a username', 'username', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var passwordC = new validation('a password confirmation', 'passwordConfirm', 'text', 'isTe
Action.c(23):     xt(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     var firstN = new validation('your first name', 'firstName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var address = new validation('your address', 'address1', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     var csz = new validation('your City/State/Zip', 'address2', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** Define the elts array:\n
Action.c(23):     ** Add a new item to the array for each object you create above\n
Action.c(23):     ** Make sure the value of the array element is the same as\n
Action.c(23):     ** the name of the object, and that the array elements are listed\n
Action.c(23):     ** in the same order the corresponding objects appear in the form\n
Action.c(23):     ** (it's more clear to the user that way)\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var elts = new Array(lastName, phoneNum, reason)\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var elts = new Array(username, password, passwordC, firstN, lastN, address, csz);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** The main function keeps track of which fields the user missed\n
Action.c(23):     ** or filled in incorrectly, and alerts the user so they can go\n
Action.c(23):     ** back and fix what's wrong.\n
Action.c(23):     ** Set allAtOnce to true if you want this "validation help" to\n
Action.c(23):     ** alert the user to all mistakes at once; set it to false if\n
Action.c(23):     ** you want it to show one mistake at a time\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var allAtOnce = true;\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** change text for alerts here\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (text): "Please include [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (other): "Please choose [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** invalid text field entries: "[field value] is an invalid [field name]!"\n
Action.c(23):     ** help with format: "Use this format: "\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertForText = "Please include ";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertGeneric = "Please choose ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endRequestAlert = ".";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginInvalidAlert = " is an invalid ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endInvalidAlert = "!";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginFormatAlert = "  Use this format: ";\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** these functions validate the string or form object passed in,\n
Action.c(23):     ** and return true or false based on whether the test succeeds or fails\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     ** validate existence of input\n

Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(23):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(23):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(23):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(23):     **     text\n
Action.c(23):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(23):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(23):     **     radio\n
Action.c(23):     **     select\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(23):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(23):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(23):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     // object definition\n
Action.c(23):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(23):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(23):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(23):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(23):     }\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ** var phoneNum = new validation('phone number', 'phoneNum', 'text', 'isPhoneNum(str)', 'x
Action.c(23):     xx-xxx-xxxx');\n
Action.c(23):     ** var reason = new validation('reason for reading this', 'reason', 'checkbox', 'isCheck(f
Action.c(23):     ormObj, form, 14, 3)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     // create objects here:\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     var username = new validation('a username', 'username', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var passwordC = new validation('a password confirmation', 'passwordConfirm', 'text', 'isTe

Action.c(23):     var address = new validation('your address', 'address1', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     var csz = new validation('your City/State/Zip', 'address2', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** Define the elts array:\n
Action.c(23):     ** Add a new item to the array for each object you create above\n
Action.c(23):     ** Make sure the value of the array element is the same as\n
Action.c(23):     ** the name of the object, and that the array elements are listed\n
Action.c(23):     ** in the same order the corresponding objects appear in the form\n
Action.c(23):     ** (it's more clear to the user that way)\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var elts = new Array(lastName, phoneNum, reason)\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var elts = new Array(username, password, passwordC, firstN, lastN, address, csz);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** The main function keeps track of which fields the user missed\n
Action.c(23):     ** or filled in incorrectly, and alerts the user so they can go\n
Action.c(23):     ** back and fix what's wrong.\n
Action.c(23):     ** Set allAtOnce to true if you want this "validation help" to\n
Action.c(23):     ** alert the user to all mistakes at once; set it to false if\n
Action.c(23):     ** you want it to show one mistake at a time\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var allAtOnce = true;\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** change text for alerts here\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (text): "Please include [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (other): "Please choose [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** invalid text field entries: "[field value] is an invalid [field name]!"\n
Action.c(23):     ** help with format: "Use this format: "\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertForText = "Please include ";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertGeneric = "Please choose ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endRequestAlert = ".";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginInvalidAlert = " is an invalid ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endInvalidAlert = "!";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginFormatAlert = "  Use this format: ";\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** these functions validate the string or form object passed in,\n
Action.c(23):     ** and return true or false based on whether the test succeeds or fails\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     ** validate existence of input\n

Action.c(23):               alert(alertText);\n
Action.c(23):             }\n

Action.c(23):             } else {\n
Action.c(23):               alertText = str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(23):             }\n

Action.c(23):               alertText += beginFormatAlert + elts[i].format + hardReturn;\n

Action.c(23):               if (firstMissingElt == null) {firstMissingElt = formObj};\n
Action.c(23):             } else {\n

Action.c(23):             }\n

Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(23):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(23):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(23):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(23):     **     text\n
Action.c(23):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(23):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(23):     **     radio\n
Action.c(23):     **     select\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(23):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(23):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(23):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     // object definition\n
Action.c(23):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(23):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(23):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(23):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(23):     }\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ** var phoneNum = new validation('phone number', 'phoneNum', 'text', 'isPhoneNum(str)', 'x
Action.c(23):     xx-xxx-xxxx');\n
Action.c(23):     ** var reason = new validation('reason for reading this', 'reason', 'checkbox', 'isCheck(f
Action.c(23):     ormObj, form, 14, 3)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     // create objects here:\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     var username = new validation('a username', 'username', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var passwordC = new validation('a password confirmation', 'passwordConfirm', 'text', 'isTe
Action.c(23):     xt(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var address = new validation('your address', 'address1', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     var csz = new validation('your City/State/Zip', 'address2', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** Define the elts array:\n
Action.c(23):     ** Add a new item to the array for each object you create above\n
Action.c(23):     ** Make sure the value of the array element is the same as\n
Action.c(23):     ** the name of the object, and that the array elements are listed\n
Action.c(23):     ** in the same order the corresponding objects appear in the form\n
Action.c(23):     ** (it's more clear to the user that way)\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var elts = new Array(lastName, phoneNum, reason)\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var elts = new Array(username, password, passwordC, firstN, lastN, address, csz);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** The main function keeps track of which fields the user missed\n
Action.c(23):     ** or filled in incorrectly, and alerts the user so they can go\n
Action.c(23):     ** back and fix what's wrong.\n
Action.c(23):     ** Set allAtOnce to true if you want this "validation help" to\n
Action.c(23):     ** alert the user to all mistakes at once; set it to false if\n
Action.c(23):     ** you want it to show one mistake at a time\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var allAtOnce = true;\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** change text for alerts here\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (text): "Please include [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (other): "Please choose [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** invalid text field entries: "[field value] is an invalid [field name]!"\n
Action.c(23):     ** help with format: "Use this format: "\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertForText = "Please include ";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertGeneric = "Please choose ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endRequestAlert = ".";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginInvalidAlert = " is an invalid ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endInvalidAlert = "!";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginFormatAlert = "  Use this format: ";\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** these functions validate the string or form object passed in,\n
Action.c(23):     ** and return true or false based on whether the test succeeds or fails\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     ** validate existence of input\n

Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(23):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(23):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(23):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(23):     **     text\n
Action.c(23):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(23):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(23):     **     radio\n
Action.c(23):     **     select\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(23):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(23):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(23):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     // object definition\n
Action.c(23):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(23):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(23):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(23):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(23):     }\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ** var phoneNum = new validation('phone number', 'phoneNum', 'text', 'isPhoneNum(str)', 'x
Action.c(23):     xx-xxx-xxxx');\n
Action.c(23):     ** var reason = new validation('reason for reading this', 'reason', 'checkbox', 'isCheck(f
Action.c(23):     ormObj, form, 14, 3)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     // create objects here:\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     var username = new validation('a username', 'username', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var passwordC = new validation('a password confirmation', 'passwordConfirm', 'text', 'isTe
Action.c(23):     xt(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     var firstN = new validation('your first name', 'firstName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var address = new validation('your address', 'address1', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     var csz = new validation('your City/State/Zip', 'address2', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** Define the elts array:\n
Action.c(23):     ** Add a new item to the array for each object you create above\n
Action.c(23):     ** Make sure the value of the array element is the same as\n
Action.c(23):     ** the name of the object, and that the array elements are listed\n
Action.c(23):     ** in the same order the corresponding objects appear in the form\n
Action.c(23):     ** (it's more clear to the user that way)\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var elts = new Array(lastName, phoneNum, reason)\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var elts = new Array(username, password, passwordC, firstN, lastN, address, csz);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** The main function keeps track of which fields the user missed\n
Action.c(23):     ** or filled in incorrectly, and alerts the user so they can go\n
Action.c(23):     ** back and fix what's wrong.\n
Action.c(23):     ** Set allAtOnce to true if you want this "validation help" to\n
Action.c(23):     ** alert the user to all mistakes at once; set it to false if\n
Action.c(23):     ** you want it to show one mistake at a time\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var allAtOnce = true;\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** change text for alerts here\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (text): "Please include [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (other): "Please choose [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** invalid text field entries: "[field value] is an invalid [field name]!"\n
Action.c(23):     ** help with format: "Use this format: "\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertForText = "Please include ";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertGeneric = "Please choose ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endRequestAlert = ".";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginInvalidAlert = " is an invalid ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endInvalidAlert = "!";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginFormatAlert = "  Use this format: ";\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** these functions validate the string or form object passed in,\n
Action.c(23):     ** and return true or false based on whether the test succeeds or fails\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     ** validate existence of input\n
Action.c(23):     **   isText(str): verifies text input or textarea is not empty\n

Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(23):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(23):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(23):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(23):     **     text\n
Action.c(23):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(23):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(23):     **     radio\n
Action.c(23):     **     select\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(23):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(23):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(23):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     // object definition\n
Action.c(23):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(23):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(23):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(23):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(23):     }\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ** var phoneNum = new validation('phone number', 'phoneNum', 'text', 'isPhoneNum(str)', 'x
Action.c(23):     xx-xxx-xxxx');\n
Action.c(23):     ** var reason = new validation('reason for reading this', 'reason', 'checkbox', 'isCheck(f
Action.c(23):     ormObj, form, 14, 3)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     // create objects here:\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     var username = new validation('a username', 'username', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var passwordC = new validation('a password confirmation', 'passwordConfirm', 'text', 'isTe
Action.c(23):     xt(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     var firstN = new validation('your first name', 'firstName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var address = new validation('your address', 'address1', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     var csz = new validation('your City/State/Zip', 'address2', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** Define the elts array:\n
Action.c(23):     ** Add a new item to the array for each object you create above\n
Action.c(23):     ** Make sure the value of the array element is the same as\n
Action.c(23):     ** the name of the object, and that the array elements are listed\n
Action.c(23):     ** in the same order the corresponding objects appear in the form\n
Action.c(23):     ** (it's more clear to the user that way)\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var elts = new Array(lastName, phoneNum, reason)\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var elts = new Array(username, password, passwordC, firstN, lastN, address, csz);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** The main function keeps track of which fields the user missed\n
Action.c(23):     ** or filled in incorrectly, and alerts the user so they can go\n
Action.c(23):     ** back and fix what's wrong.\n
Action.c(23):     ** Set allAtOnce to true if you want this "validation help" to\n
Action.c(23):     ** alert the user to all mistakes at once; set it to false if\n
Action.c(23):     ** you want it to show one mistake at a time\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var allAtOnce = true;\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** change text for alerts here\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (text): "Please include [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (other): "Please choose [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** invalid text field entries: "[field value] is an invalid [field name]!"\n
Action.c(23):     ** help with format: "Use this format: "\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertForText = "Please include ";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertGeneric = "Please choose ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endRequestAlert = ".";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginInvalidAlert = " is an invalid ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endInvalidAlert = "!";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginFormatAlert = "  Use this format: ";\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** these functions validate the string or form object passed in,\n
Action.c(23):     ** and return true or false based on whether the test succeeds or fails\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     ** validate existence of input\n

Action.c(23):               alert(alertText);\n
Action.c(23):             }\n

Action.c(23):               alertText += str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(23):             } else {\n
Action.c(23):               alertText = str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(23):             }\n

Action.c(23):               alertText += beginFormatAlert + elts[i].format + hardReturn;\n

Action.c(23):               if (firstMissingElt == null) {firstMissingElt = formObj};\n
Action.c(23):             } else {\n

Action.c(23):             }\n

Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(23):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(23):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(23):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(23):     **     text\n
Action.c(23):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(23):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(23):     **     radio\n
Action.c(23):     **     select\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(23):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(23):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(23):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     // object definition\n
Action.c(23):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(23):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(23):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(23):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(23):     }\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ** var phoneNum = new validation('phone number', 'phoneNum', 'text', 'isPhoneNum(str)', 'x
Action.c(23):     xx-xxx-xxxx');\n
Action.c(23):     ** var reason = new validation('reason for reading this', 'reason', 'checkbox', 'isCheck(f
Action.c(23):     ormObj, form, 14, 3)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     // create objects here:\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     var username = new validation('a username', 'username', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var passwordC = new validation('a password confirmation', 'passwordConfirm', 'text', 'isTe
Action.c(23):     xt(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var address = new validation('your address', 'address1', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     var csz = new validation('your City/State/Zip', 'address2', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** Define the elts array:\n
Action.c(23):     ** Add a new item to the array for each object you create above\n
Action.c(23):     ** Make sure the value of the array element is the same as\n
Action.c(23):     ** the name of the object, and that the array elements are listed\n
Action.c(23):     ** in the same order the corresponding objects appear in the form\n
Action.c(23):     ** (it's more clear to the user that way)\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var elts = new Array(lastName, phoneNum, reason)\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var elts = new Array(username, password, passwordC, firstN, lastN, address, csz);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** The main function keeps track of which fields the user missed\n
Action.c(23):     ** or filled in incorrectly, and alerts the user so they can go\n
Action.c(23):     ** back and fix what's wrong.\n
Action.c(23):     ** Set allAtOnce to true if you want this "validation help" to\n
Action.c(23):     ** alert the user to all mistakes at once; set it to false if\n
Action.c(23):     ** you want it to show one mistake at a time\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var allAtOnce = true;\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** change text for alerts here\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (text): "Please include [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (other): "Please choose [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** invalid text field entries: "[field value] is an invalid [field name]!"\n
Action.c(23):     ** help with format: "Use this format: "\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertForText = "Please include ";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertGeneric = "Please choose ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endRequestAlert = ".";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginInvalidAlert = " is an invalid ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endInvalidAlert = "!";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginFormatAlert = "  Use this format: ";\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** these functions validate the string or form object passed in,\n
Action.c(23):     ** and return true or false based on whether the test succeeds or fails\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     ** validate existence of input\n

Action.c(23):         realName = elts[i].realName;\n

Action.c(23):           str = formObj.value;\n

Action.c(23):     \n

Action.c(23):             } else {\n
Action.c(23):               alertText = beginRequestAlertForText + realName + endRequestAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(23):               alert(alertText);\n
Action.c(23):             }\n
Action.c(23):           } else {\n
Action.c(23):             if (allAtOnce) {\n
Action.c(23):               alertText += str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(23):             } else {\n
Action.c(23):               alertText = str + beginInvalidAlert + realName + endInvalidAlert + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(23):             }\n
Action.c(23):             if (elts[i].format != null) {\n
Action.c(23):               alertText += beginFormatAlert + elts[i].format + hardReturn;\n
Action.c(23):             }\n
Action.c(23):             if (allAtOnce) {\n
Action.c(23):               if (firstMissingElt == null) {firstMissingElt = formObj};\n
Action.c(23):             } else {\n
Action.c(23):               alert(alertText);\n
Action.c(23):             }\n
Action.c(23):           }\n

Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** define and instantiate validation objects\n
Action.c(23):     ** the validation object accepts the following parameters:\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   realName: name used in the alerts (same as label on the page)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   formEltName: this must be the name of the corresponding\n
Action.c(23):     **       HTML form element; make it the same as the object name\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   eltType: element type (we have to create this since IE3\n
Action.c(23):     **       doesn't support the type property for for elements)\n
Action.c(23):     **     text\n
Action.c(23):     **     textarea\n
Action.c(23):     **     checkbox\n
Action.c(23):     **     radio\n
Action.c(23):     **     select\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   uptoSnuff: function call that's evaluated during validation check\n
Action.c(23):     **     isText(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isSelect(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isRadio(formObj)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isCheck(formObj, form, [index of first checkbox in group],\n
Action.c(23):     **         [number of checkboxes])\n
Action.c(23):     **     isEmail(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isState(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isZipCode(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isPhoneNum(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **     isDate(str)\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     **   format: text representation of required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       pass 'null' if no required format;\n
Action.c(23):     **       used in alert as an aid to user\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     // object definition\n
Action.c(23):     function validation(realName, formEltName, eltType, upToSnuff, format) {\n
Action.c(23):       this.realName = realName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.formEltName = formEltName;\n
Action.c(23):       this.eltType = eltType;\n
Action.c(23):       this.upToSnuff = upToSnuff;\n
Action.c(23):       this.format = format;\n
Action.c(23):     }\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** create a new object for each form element you need to validate\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var lastName = new validation('last name', 'lastName', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ** var phoneNum = new validation('phone number', 'phoneNum', 'text', 'isPhoneNum(str)', 'x
Action.c(23):     xx-xxx-xxxx');\n
Action.c(23):     ** var reason = new validation('reason for reading this', 'reason', 'checkbox', 'isCheck(f
Action.c(23):     ormObj, form, 14, 3)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     // create objects here:\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     var username = new validation('a username', 'username', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var passwordC = new validation('a password confirmation', 'passwordConfirm', 'text', 'isTe
Action.c(23):     xt(str)', null);\n

Action.c(23):     var address = new validation('your address', 'address1', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     var csz = new validation('your City/State/Zip', 'address2', 'text', 'isText(str)', null);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** Define the elts array:\n
Action.c(23):     ** Add a new item to the array for each object you create above\n
Action.c(23):     ** Make sure the value of the array element is the same as\n
Action.c(23):     ** the name of the object, and that the array elements are listed\n
Action.c(23):     ** in the same order the corresponding objects appear in the form\n
Action.c(23):     ** (it's more clear to the user that way)\n
Action.c(23):     ** for example:\n
Action.c(23):     ** var elts = new Array(lastName, phoneNum, reason)\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var elts = new Array(username, password, passwordC, firstN, lastN, address, csz);\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** The main function keeps track of which fields the user missed\n
Action.c(23):     ** or filled in incorrectly, and alerts the user so they can go\n
Action.c(23):     ** back and fix what's wrong.\n
Action.c(23):     ** Set allAtOnce to true if you want this "validation help" to\n
Action.c(23):     ** alert the user to all mistakes at once; set it to false if\n
Action.c(23):     ** you want it to show one mistake at a time\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var allAtOnce = true;\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** change text for alerts here\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (text): "Please include [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** unspecified field (other): "Please choose [field name]."\n
Action.c(23):     ** invalid text field entries: "[field value] is an invalid [field name]!"\n
Action.c(23):     ** help with format: "Use this format: "\n
Action.c(23):     ***************************************************************/\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertForText = "Please include ";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginRequestAlertGeneric = "Please choose ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endRequestAlert = ".";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginInvalidAlert = " is an invalid ";\n
Action.c(23):     var endInvalidAlert = "!";\n
Action.c(23):     var beginFormatAlert = "  Use this format: ";\n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     \n
Action.c(23):     /***************************************************************\n
Action.c(23):     ** these functions validate the string or form object passed in,\n
Action.c(23):     ** and return true or false based on whether the test succeeds or fails\n
Action.c(23):     **\n
Action.c(23):     ** validate existence of input\n

Action.c(23):             } else {\n

Action.c(23):             }\n

Action.c(23):               if (firstMissingElt == null) {firstMissingElt = formObj};\n

Action.c(23):             }\n
